## Nemetic Phi — Karma Bija Selflessness (S120)

### Nemetic String

Φ(Karma_Bija_Selflessness) = σ(intentional_attention|habitual_distraction) ∘ ρ(rasa_emotion|mechanical_repetition) ∘ λ(kriya_enactment|passive_reception) ∘ β(seed_sprouting|dormant_potential) ∘ δγ(karmic_loam|antahkarana_substrate) ∘ μ(mantra_structure|entropic_noise) + ε | :conscious_planting

### Operator Breakdown

**σ — Air / Aerunik (emphasis: 0.65)**
Intentional attention as the directing force of seed-planting. Aerunik governs mantra not as mechanical recitation but as directed awareness — the quality of attention brought to an action determines the potency of the karmic seed planted. Habitual distraction scatters bija across the inner landscape without pattern or purpose; intentional presence plants with precision. The moderate emphasis reflects that attention is necessary but insufficient without emotional depth and physical enactment.

**ρ — Water / Sentaria (emphasis: 0.74)**
Rasa — the emotional coloring, the juice, the felt quality — determines whether a karmic seed carries vitality or remains husk. Sentaria governs the difference between selfless action performed with genuine devotion and the same action performed mechanically. A seed planted with rasa contains emotional life-force; one planted through mere repetition may technically exist but lacks the moisture to sprout vigorously. Selflessness itself is a rasa quality: the emotional orientation toward service rather than accumulation.

**λ — Fire / Jvalion (emphasis: 0.70)**
Kriya as enactment — karma literally means action, and without enactment there is no seed. Jvalion provides the activation energy: thinking about selfless service plants no seeds; performing it does. The fire element also governs the tapas (austerity) dimension: selfless action burns away ego-attachment, transforming the actor even as it plants seeds for future consequence. The fire purifies intention through the discipline of doing.

**β — Wood / Arboriel (emphasis: 0.83)**
The dominant operator. Seed sprouting is the central metaphor and the central reality of karma-bija. Arboriel governs the organic unfolding from bija (seed) to phala (fruit) — the temporal arc through which present action determines future experience. Every repetition of cultural code, every selfless act, every mantra recitation plants seeds in the antahkarana that will sprout as behavior, tendency, and circumstance. The wood element captures the patient, organic, non-mechanical quality of karmic development: seeds grow in their own time, by their own logic.

**δγ — Earth / Humavita (emphasis: 0.80)**
Karmic loam — the cultural inheritance and personal history that constitutes the soil in which new seeds root. Humavita holds the antahkarana as the inner instrument conditioned by generations of prior planting. The soil is not neutral; it carries the accumulated karma-bija of ancestors, culture, and personal past. New seeds planted selflessly must contend with, and gradually transform, this inherited ground. The high emphasis reflects that no seed exists in isolation — it grows in soil shaped by everything that came before.

**μ — Metal / Ferrosid (emphasis: 0.58)**
Mantra structure provides the formal scaffolding — the repetitive, syllabic precision that gives karmic intention shape. Ferrosid ensures that seed-planting has form rather than remaining diffuse aspiration. However, the lowest emphasis reflects that structure without rasa and attention is mere mechanism. The metal serves the organic process rather than governing it.

### Z-State

**conscious_planting** — The system resolves toward deliberate, aware, emotionally sincere action that plants karmic seeds with intention rather than scattering them through habitual unconsciousness.

### Tendency

**β → 0.83** — The system's strongest pull is toward organic unfolding. The framework insists that karma operates on seed-logic: patient, generational, temporal, irreducibly organic. Understanding karma is understanding growth.

# CE-STATE: multiscale
# EI-NOTE: Causal power distributed across multiple description levels
